	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64609341"><p>Right, the headline is misleading because it's not actually Android at all. It's a custom OS built on the Android Open Source Project (ASOP), but can't carry the Android name or branding because it doesn't have Google's services installed. Those services are mostly blocked in China, so domestic manufacturers replace them with their own.</p><p>I guess whoever wrote the headline probably had difficulty choosing to imply that Android was insecure, or Huawei was insecure. Both make such great clickbait.</p></div>
	</div>

