	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64609389">I don't think the problem is the availability of the app. I think the problem is that no app can be secure if the hardware platform and/or OS are backdoored.
<p>
Android in China is not Google's, nor are the hardware platforms. iPhone and Android+ Google Play are inspected, reviewed, and signed/encrypted from the moment they are made.
</p><p>
I believe the push for Windows 11 to require the tpm security chip is to force PCs to be a more closed platform like phones, with everything from the BIOS up "trusted" by signin<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

